The paper focuses on person retrieval in surveillance systems, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). It also involves large-scale data and evaluation methods, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The competition aspect suggests a potential connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and security and privacy (cs.CR).
